The paper discusses collaborative filtering, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) for building recommender systems. The focus of the paper is on parallel and distributed implementations, which are often used in distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges and issues related to collaborative filtering, which are relevant to database systems (cs.DB).
